<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-11-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="826" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d826">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">857.014/57</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-11-21">November 21, 1928</date>.<lb/>[Received
                                December 4.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 3189</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that in an
                            official reply to a question in the House of Commons on November 19,
                            1928, the Under <pb facs="0834" n="716" xml:id="pg_716"/> Secretary of
                            State for Foreign Affairs stated that after a careful review of all the
                            issues involved, and having regard to the friendly relations existing
                            between the two countries, His Majesty’s Government have decided to
                            waive the British claim to Bouvet Island in favor of Norway.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Ambassador:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ray
                                    Atherton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>